heaviest_rainrate.status: Today ranked 10th for the heaviest rainfall ever in our records, with a peak intensity of 10.1mm per hour sustained for 16.6 hours, resulting in a total accumulation of 9.37mm.  The heaviest rain rate registered stands at 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  21.19mm fell during the storm over 15.0 hours.

longest_rain.status: Today, one rain storm lasted for 16.6 hours (ranking 10th for longest storm from our records).  It accumulated 9.37mm of rain and it fell at 10.1mm per hour at times.  The record duration for continuous rain was set on 04 January 2025, the storm lasted 37.2 hours with a total precipitation of 36.8mm and it reached 4.6mm per hour at times.
